Version: 0.1.7
Date: 2026-04-12

Changes:
- Existing-repo generated map bootstrap:
  when a project has no real `AGENTS.md`, Merlion now auto-generates
  layered fallback maps under `.merlion/maps` on new session start,
  then uses them in orientation and path-guided loading.
- Path-guided context loading:
  runtime now collects path signals from tool calls/results and injects
  incremental AGENTS guidance along `root -> target` directory chains,
  avoiding repeated broad repository scans.
- Layered AGENTS map contract:
  added MANUAL/AUTO section protocol and seeded root/runtime/builtin
  AGENTS maps for path-scoped navigation.
- Commit-time AGENTS maintenance pipeline:
  added `scripts/agents/update.ts` + `scripts/agents/lint.ts`, git hooks
  (`pre-commit`, `pre-push`), and npm scripts for update/lint/drift checks.
- UX map update signal:
  CLI now emits compact `[map] ...` lines when guidance/index maps are
  updated during a turn.
- E2E coverage additions:
  added lifecycle tests for path-guidance chain loading and AGENTS auto
  maintenance update/lint/check-drift flow.

